full_title: Good Luck, Babe! by Chappell Roan
title: Good Luck, Babe!

description.plain:
On “Good Luck, Babe!”, Chappell looks back on a secret relationship with a woman from her past and the struggle with compulsory heterosexuality that ultimately broke them up.

During a show in San Diego, Chappell performed “Good Luck, Babe!” for the first time. She would later post snippets to social media before confirming the April 5th release date.

Given Chappell’s love of referencing 2000s movies in her song/album artwork (Mean Girls, Bedazzled, Jennifer’s Body, etc.), her pig-nosed look in the cover art is likely a reference to Penelope, a 2006 movie about a girl cursed to have a pig nose until she meets someone who loves her as she truly is. The film, like this song, deals with themes of self-acceptance when it comes to love and Penelope’s struggle is similar to that of the muse of this song, who is running from who she truly is.
